# VERSION
v0.15.3

# Changelog
- v0.15.3
    - Fixed scheduler never auto-firing cron tasks: the 60s poll ticker is not wall-clock aligned, so exact-second `shouldFire` matching missed every fire point (e.g. `0 0 */2 * * *`). `scan` now window-matches `(lastTick, now]` and schedules at the matched second; the first tick establishes a baseline without backfilling.
    - Added `GET /api/v1/tasks/cron-preview?expr=&n=3` to preview the next N future fire times of a cron expression.
- v0.15.2
    - Added docs/system_design/2026-07-20 FINANCIAL_FEATURE_PACK_V1_HANDS_ON_GUIDE.md.
- v0.15.1
    - Upgraded infro to v0.18.4.
- v0.15.0
    - Migrated cronjob to postgresql.
- v0.14.4
    - Migrated bars sql.
    - Upgraded cronjob to v0.18.3.
- v0.14.3
    - Updated `docs/2026-05-07 CONFIG_OF_CRONJOB_AND_ARTEMIS.md`: expanded task.yaml parameter documentation with types, formats, and examples for all tasks; marked resolved issues
    - Updated config doc: `STOCK_ZH_A_MKT_CATEGORY` → `STOCK_ZH_A_MKT_CATEGORY_MAIRUI` (aligned with Artemis rename)
    - Updated config doc: `STOCK_ZH_A_INDUSTRY_WEIGHT_SWHY` and `STOCK_ZH_A_INDUSTRY_DAILY_SWHY` now OrchestratorUnit (split per index); added `_CHILD` internal tasks to task directory and internal tasks section
- v0.14.2
    - Fixed task import failing on re-import after soft-delete: reactivate soft-deleted tasks by updating all fields and setting deleted=0, instead of hard-deleting (which was blocked by FK constraint from task_runs).
- v0.14.1
    - Fixed inconsistent time in task_run table.
- v0.14.0
    - Added task cancel to remote service.
- v0.13.5
    - Added config in config doc
- v0.13.4
    - Renamed documents of cronjob.
    - Added documents of 2026-04-01 FEATURE_EXTEND_RUNNING_STRATEGY.
- v0.13.3
    - Added export and import for tasks.
    - Fixed cancel for callback tasks.
    - Added existed tasks checking.
- v0.13.2
    - Updated deployment scripts to support auto proxy.
- v0.13.1
    - Added config doc for cronjob.
- v0.13.0
    - Involve HTTP client component from infra framework to support http request in cronjob executor.
    - Upgraded infra framework version to v0.16.2
    - Support multiple downstream invocation in cronjob.
    - Using target service and target path to replace target URL.
    - Optimized executor flow.
    - Added new clients query for frontend to fetch available target services and their APIs.
    - Removed timeout seconds from task run.
- v0.12.13
    - Fixed bug of missing traceid after task entered in channel.
    - Involve http client component from infra framework.
    - Dropped pass ip & port in meta of cronjob executor request.
- v0.12.12
    - Fixed bug of failed updating request body of task.
    - Fixed missing record of cronjob req to downstream.
    - Fixed missing fields when updating request header and body.
- v0.12.11
    - Removed callback ip & port from header of cronjob executor request and set them in meta.
    - Upgraded infra version to v0.16.2
- v0.12.10
    - Adjusted the failure judgement logic in executor: Failed/succeed is determined by response code and msg together.
- v0.12.9
    - Fixed bug of when async task finalized callback but got wrong response code and status.
- v0.12.8
    - Extend callback_time_scanner functionality to a assembled scanner, which support sync/async/progress callback.
    - Sync run stuck config is added.
    - Graceful clean-up is added in new Scanner as well.
- v0.12.7
    - Replaced jenkins deployment and use python as a substitute.
